params._router: The address of the Equito router used for cross-chain messaging.

createProposal(uint256,uint256,uint256,s.details: Naming in the contracts and FE:      `sourceChain` = the chain the user is currently connected.      `originChain` = the chain a proposal was created, can be different from `sourceChain` at FE runtime.      `destinationChain` = the chain where `_receiveMessageFromPeers` gets called.

params.destinationChainSelector: The chain selector where the proposal is being sent.
params.endTimestamp: The timestamp when the proposal will end.
params.originChainSelector: The chain selector where the proposal originates.
params.title: The title of the proposal.
params.tokenName: The name of the token used for voting.

deleteProposalById(bytes32).details: If there are too many proposals, this function can run out of gas.      In that case, call `deleteProposalByIndexOptimized` which will      run more efficiently but it will not maintain the array order.

params.proposalId: The ID of the proposal to delete.

deleteProposalByIndex(uint256).details: If there are too many proposals, this function can run out of gas.      In that case, call `deleteProposalByIndexOptimized` which will      run more efficiently but it will not maintain the array order.

params.proposalIndex: The index of the proposal to delete.

deleteProposalByIndexOptimized(uint256).details: Does not maintain the original array order.

params.proposalIndex: The index of the proposal to delete.

params.chainSelectors: An array of chain selectors associated with the token data.
params.tokenName: The name of the token to delete.

getAmountDelegatedTokens(address,address.details: We use `isGetPastVotesEnabled` to control wheather we want to retrive a past voting power

params.isGetPastVotesEnabled: A flag indicating whether to get past votes or current votes.

returns._0: uint256 The amount of tokens delegated.

getSlicedReversedProposals(int256,int256.details: Used to display the newest proposals first with pagination.

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

params.messageData: The data of the message received.

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby disabling any functionality that is only available to the owner.

params.newCreateProposalFee: The new creation fee value, in wei.

params.addresses: The list of addresses corresponding to the chain selectors.

setTokenData(string,uint256[],address[]).details: Will be queried during voting to ensure the provided token matches		 the proposal token across different chains.

params.chainSelectors: An array of chain selectors for the token.
params.tokenAddresses: An array of addresses for the token.

params.newVoteOnProposalFee: The new vote-on-proposal fee value, in wei.

params.destination: The address to receive the native token.

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

params.chainSelector: The chain selector for the token data.
params.tokenAddress: The address associated with the token.
params.tokenName: The name of the token to update.

voteOnProposal(uint256,bytes32,uint256,u.details: `tokenAddress` will be validated in `_receiveMessageFromPeers._voteOnProposal` and      votes will only be counted if it's valid.

params.destinationChainSelector: The chain selector where the vote is being sent.
params.numVotes: The number of votes to cast.
params.proposalId: The ID of the proposal being voted on.
params.tokenAddress: The address of the token used for voting.

createProposalFee().notice: Protocol fee for creating proposals,         small value for us to simulate on Equito Builder Program.

deleteProposalById(bytes32).notice: Deletes a proposal by its ID.

deleteProposalByIndex(uint256).notice: Deletes a proposal at a specified index.

deleteProposalByIndexOptimized(uint256).notice: Deletes a proposal at a specified index.

deleteTokenData(string,uint256[]).notice: Deletes the token data for a given token.

getAmountDelegatedTokens(address,address.notice: Returns the amount of tokens delegated to a user at a specific proposal.

getProposalIdsLength().notice: Get the length of all proposals.

getSlicedProposals(uint256,uint256).notice: Build up an array of proposals and return it using the index params.

getSlicedReversedProposals(int256,int256.notice: Build up an array of proposals in reverse order.

getSlicedTokenNames(uint256,uint256).notice: The the tokens name via pagination.

getTokenNamesLength().notice: Get the length of all tokens.

receiveMessage((uint256,uint256,(bytes32.notice: Receives a cross-chain message from the Router Contract.         It is a wrapper function for the `_receiveMessage` functions, that need to be overridden.         Only the Router Contract is allowed to call this function.

setCreateProposalFee(uint256).notice: Sets the creation fee for a proposal.

setPeers(uint256[],(bytes32,bytes32)[]).notice: Allows the owner to set the peer addresses for different chain selectors.

setTokenData(string,uint256[],address[]).notice: Set token data to be used in proposals.

setVoteOnProposalFee(uint256).notice: Sets the fee for voting on a proposal.

tokenData(string,uint256).notice: Token data used as a security mechanism.

transferFee(address).notice: Move the native token stored in this contract.

updateTokenData(string,uint256,address).notice: Updates the token data for a given token.

userVotes(address,bytes32).notice: Amount of user votes for each proposal.

voteOnProposalFee().notice: Protocol fee for voting on proposals,         small value for us to simulate on Equito Builder Program.
